Notes :

- if java is encountering a error in a particular line, it stopes the entire program and doesnt execute the lines below it.
- if java is encountering a error in a particular line, the entire program will terminate. it wont go to the next line
- to make the erroless code execute, we need exception handling.
- error in programming is called as exception. 
- two types : complie time and run time exception. 
